The prediction task is to determine whether a person makes over $50K a year. Dataset

4. Data Overview¶

Data dictionary¶

  • age: continuous.
  • workclass: Private, Self-emp-not-inc, Self-emp-inc, Federal-gov, Local-gov, State-gov, Without-pay, Never-worked.
  • fnlwgt: continuous.
  • education: Bachelors, Some-college, 11th, HS-grad, Prof-school, Assoc-acdm, Assoc-voc, 9th, 7th-8th, 12th, Masters, 1st-4th, 10th, Doctorate, 5th-6th, Preschool.
  • education.num: continuous.
  • marital.status: Married-civ-spouse, Divorced, Never-married, Separated, Widowed, Married-spouse-absent, Married-AF-spouse.
  • occupation: Tech-support, Craft-repair, Other-service, Sales, Exec-managerial, Prof-specialty, Handlers-cleaners, Machine-op-inspct, Adm-clerical, Farming-fishing, Transport-moving, Priv-house-serv, Protective-serv, Armed-Forces.
  • relationship: Wife, Own-child, Husband, Not-in-family, Other-relative, Unmarried.
  • race: White, Asian-Pac-Islander, Amer-Indian-Eskimo, Other, Black.
  • sex: Female, Male.
  • capital.gain: continuous.
  • capital.loss: continuous.
  • hours.per.week: continuous.
  • native.country: United-States, Cambodia, England, Puerto-Rico, Canada, Germany, Outlying-US(Guam-USVI-etc), India, Japan, Greece, South, China, Cuba, Iran, Honduras, Philippines, Italy, Poland, Jamaica, Vietnam, Mexico, Portugal, Ireland, France, Dominican-Republic, Laos, Ecuador, Taiwan, Haiti, Columbia, Hungary, Guatemala, Nicaragua, Scotland, Thailand, Yugoslavia, El-Salvador, Trinadad&Tobago, Peru, Hong, Holand-Netherlands.
  • There are 32561 instances and 15 features in the dataset.

In [33]:
new_data = data.copy()
In [34]:
new_data['workclass'].replace(to_replace=['Without-pay', 'Never-worked', 'Unknown'], value='Other', inplace=True)
new_data.loc[new_data['workclass'].isin(['Federal-gov', 'Local-gov', 'State-gov']), 'workclass'] = 'Government'
new_data.loc[new_data['workclass'].str.startswith('Self-emp'), 'workclass'] = 'Self-employed'
  • Self-employed work class have the highest percentage of people who earn >50K.

6.31. Conclusion¶

  1. The older a person is the more likely will have a higher income.
  2. Majority of many people belong to Private work class. Self-emp-inc people have the highest percentage of those who earn >50K.
  3. Final weight have a small influence on income.
  4. The features such as education and education.num are giving the same information. Percentage of people who earn >50K increases as the years of education increase. So, can be left only one of the two.
  5. The features such as marital.status and relationship are giving the similar information. People who Married-civ-spouse or Married-AF-spouse have the highest percentage of those who earn >50K. So, can be left only one of the two.
  6. People with occupations such as Exec-managerial and Prof-specialty have the highest percentage of those who earn >50K.
  7. Can't say that race has a large influence on income because quite many people are White race.
  8. Percentage of those who earn >50K is large among females than males.
  9. Majority of people have capital gain and loss equal to zero. Can be observed that they are larger in those people who earn >50K than <=50K.
  10. Quite many people work 40 hours per week. Can be observed that percentage of people who earn >50K increases as the work hours per week increase.
  11. Can't say that native country has a large influence on income because quite many people come from the United-States.
